The paper deals with the construction and analysis of Boolean functions with resilience properties, which are important in cryptography, distributed computing, and pseudorandomness. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to these areas, such as cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
